[30;1m1596 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m1597 | [0m[35m# The vcs_version target is defined and registered here in the python backend because the VCS[0m
[30;1m1598 | [0m[35m# version functionality uses a lot of python machinery in its implementation, and because it is[0m
[30;1m1599 | [0m[35m# (at least at the time of writing) highly unlikely to be used outside a python context in practice.[0m
[30;1m1600 | [0m[35m# However, hypothetically, the source file generated by a vcs_version target can be in any language.[0m
[30;1m1601 | [0m[35m# Therefore any language-specific fields (such as python_resolve) are registered as plugin fields[0m
[30;1m1602 | [0m[35m# instead of provided directly here, even though the only language in question is python.[0m

[30;1m251 | [0m[35m            (The algorithm used for dedention simply looks at the first indented line and[0m
[30;1m252 | [0m[35m            unambiguously tries to strip that much indentation from every indented line thereafter.)[0m
[30;1m253 | [0m[35m        - Replaces all occurrences of multiple spaces in a sentence with a single space[0m
[30;1m254 | [0m[35m        - Replaces all occurrences of multiple newlines with exactly 2 newlines[0m

[30;1m257 | [0m[35m    # NB: We don't cache this process at any level for two reasons:[0m
[30;1m258 | [0m[35m    #   1. Several tools (including pex) refer to Python at an absolute path, so a named cache is[0m
[30;1m259 | [0m[35m    #   the only way for this to work reasonably well. Since the named cache could be wiped between[0m
